# The committed catalog/artifacts are byte-compared against deriveCatalog's output
# (LF). Pin them to LF on checkout so a Windows working tree (core.autocrlf=true)
# doesn't turn them into CRLF and break `bun run check:catalog` locally (CI on Linux
# is unaffected). Scoped to the compared artifacts to avoid a repo-wide renormalization;
# run `git add --renormalize .` under `* text=auto eol=lf` separately if you want LF everywhere.
.claude-plugin/marketplace.json text eol=lf
dist/marketplace.pinned.json text eol=lf
